BT428 Analysis

BT428 - Shannon Diversity

cols <- grep("BT428",names(s),value=T);
grps <- factor(gsub("BT428_|_R[1234]$","",cols),levels=c("INVITRO_P0","INVITRO_CON","INVITRO_TR","INVIVO_P0","ENG","MRD_CON","MRD_R","MRD_T","MRD_TR","REC_CON","REC_R","REC_T","REC_TR","TR_RETRANS_CON","TR_RETRANS_P0","TR_RETRANS_TR"));
sums <- apply( co.2[,cols] > 0,2,sum );
maxes <- apply( co.2[,cols],2,max );

df <- data.frame( Diversity=s[cols],Groups=grps,Sums=sums,MaxCloneSize=maxes );

ggplot( df, aes(x=Groups,y=Diversity)) + 
  geom_boxplot( colour="black" ) +
  geom_jitter( colour="red", height=0, width=0.20 ) +
  theme_pubr() +
  labs( title="BT428 Shannon Diversity Index" ) +
  theme(axis.text.x = element_text(angle = 90, vjust = 0.5, hjust=1));

Plot BC size by rank??

l <- list();
for (grp in unique(grps)) {
  
  if (sum( grps == grp ) < 2) next;
  tmp <- as.data.frame(apply( co.2[,cols[ grps == grp ]],2,sort,decreasing=T ));
  colnames(tmp) <- gsub(".+_(R[0-4]+)$","\\1",colnames(tmp));
  tmp2 <- gather( tmp, key="Replicate",value="Fraction" ) %>% 
    filter( Fraction > 0 ) %>% 
    group_by( Replicate ) %>% 
    mutate(Rank=rank(desc(Fraction)));

  l[[grp]] <- tmp2 %>% ggplot( aes( x=Rank,y=Fraction,color=Replicate )) +
    geom_line() +
    geom_point() +
    scale_y_log10( name="Fraction of Population", limits=c(min(tmp2$Fraction),1)) +
    scale_x_log10( name="Clone Rank") +
    labs( title=grp, color="" ) +
    theme_pubr( legend=c(0.8,0.8) );
  
}

Prepare line plots for BT428

l2 <- list();
newGrps <- list();
newGrps[["INVITRO"]] <- c("ENG","INVITRO_P0","INVITRO_CON","INVIVO_P0");
newGrps[["MRD"]] <- c("MRD_CON","MRD_R","MRD_T","MRD_TR");
newGrps[["REC"]] <- c("REC_CON","REC_R","REC_T","REC_TR");
newGrps[["RETRANS"]] <- c("TR_RETRANS_P0","TR_RETRANS_CON","TR_RETRANS_TR");

for (grpL in names(newGrps)) {

  if (sum( grps == grp ) < 2) next;
  tmp <- as.data.frame(apply( co.2[,cols[ grps %in% newGrps[[grpL]]] ],2,sort,decreasing=T ));
  tmp2 <- gather( tmp, key="Replicate",value="Fraction" ) %>% filter( Fraction > 0 ) %>% 
    group_by( Replicate ) %>% mutate(CloneFreq=rank(desc(Fraction)));
  tmp2$Color <- sapply( tmp2$Replicate, function(x) grps[ which( cols == x )]);

  l2[[grpL]] <- tmp2 %>% ggplot( aes( x=log10(Fraction),y=CloneFreq,group=Replicate,color=Color )) +
      geom_line( lwd=1 ) +
      scale_y_log10( name="Clones  \u0192" ) +
      xlim( NA, 0 ) + xlab("Clonal Frequency") + 
      labs( title="BT428",color="Sample Group" ) +
      theme_pubr( legend=c(0.8,0.8) );
  
}

BT428 - In Vitro

l2[["INVITRO"]];

BT428 - MRD

What these lineplots seem to show is the following:
  • Each of the BT428 MRD samples seems to have the same number of total barcodes - just over 10k
  • Radiation Tx seems to push a number of clones down, providing minor selection pressure
  • TMZ Tx (alone or combined with radiation) seems to dramatically push the distribution down, as reflected in the larger horizontal portion at the top-left of the curves, and also seems to reduce the largest clone sizes compared to the control or radiation-only samples (bottom right of curves) 
l2[["MRD"]];

BT428 - Recurrences

As was stated above, the BT428 Recurrence Control and Radiation-only samples start with the same number of clones as the MRD samples (just over 10k), but only the TMZ-treated samples have a reduced number of clones (between 1k & 5k). The combination treatment MAY have a slightly stronger effect than TMZ alone.

However, the samples treated with TMZ (alone or in combination) both seem to be becoming more clonal, as evidenced at the bottom-right side of the curves.

l2[["REC"]];

BT428 - TR Retransplanted

As in the previous plot, the samples here are TR-treated and then retransplanted. They also show ~1000 detectable clones, which agrees with the above plot. What I see in both the control and treated samples is a decrease in the clonal frequency for the low-abundance clones (green and blue curves both shift left compared to pink at the top left), and both green and blue curves shift right at the upper end (bottom right), indicating a more clonal population than the P0. Since this happens in both the control (CON) and TMZ+Radiation samples, and to the same degree, this must be a function of time, not treatment.

l2[["RETRANS"]];
